CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A3 reads:"Last Rites for Kappa Alpha Psi Founder - Funeral services were held for Dr. Marcus P. Blakemore, one of the 10 founders of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, from Ebenezer Baptist Church on Tuesday. He had practiced dentistry here for 35 years.  Death came on Oct. 8 in Pittsburgh Veterans Administration Hospital...Right photo: H.H. Holloway, executive secretary of Kappa Alpha Psi, center, and flower escort outside the church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: H. H. Holloway standing in between two unknown women holding funeral floral arrangements inscribed Kappa Alpha Psi, in front of Ebenezer Baptist Church for funeral of Dr. Marcus P. Blakemore
